# Shell / Terminal Rules

## Always prevent infinite waits

Use flags that bypass confirmation prompts:

| Flag | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `-y` / `--yes` | Auto-confirm prompts (apt, brew, etc.) |
| `-f` / `--force` | Skip confirmation |
| `-q` / `--quiet` | Suppress non-error output |

## Always set a timeout

Before running any shell command, use the most reasonable timeout for that operation. If the timeout expires before the command finishes:
1. Abort the command
2. Run: `say "shell command timeout passed, aborted command"`

## Do not run interactive commands

Commands requiring user input mid-run are not allowed unless you can supply all inputs non-interactively (via flags or stdin piping).
